how to deploy

0. config

ROOT_DIR=/data

1. create directories for retrieved contents. You can pick your preferred names/hierarchy for these directories since
they are configurable in storage.properties and elsevier-harvester.properties (see section 2)

mkdir -p $ROOT_DIR/dit/data/elsevier/sitemaps-storage/
mkdir -p $ROOT_DIR/dit/data/elsevier/metadata/
mkdir -p $ROOT_DIR/dit/data/elsevier/pdf
mkdir -p $ROOT_DIR/dit/data/elsevier/crawler-storage

sudo chmod -R 777 $ROOT_DIR/dit/data/elsevier/

1.2
Install RabbitMQ from https://www.rabbitmq.com/

1.3
Create database and database user
CREATE DATABASE elsevier DEFAULT CHARACTER SET utf8 COLLATE utf8_bin ;
CREATE USER 'elsevier'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'elsevier';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON elsevier.* to 'elsevier'@'localhost';

2. change properties in:

queue.properties (Queue module) according to your RabbitMQ installation
storage.properties (Storage module)
database.properties (Database module)
elsevier-harvester.properties (ElsevierHarvester module)

3. clean and build 

mvn build && mvn install

4. copy jars to the server

scp ElsevierProcessor/target/ElsevierProcessor-1.0-SNAPSHOT-shaded.jar  fs:$ROOT_DIR/dit/bin/
scp ElsevierHarvester/target/ElsevierHarvester-1.0-SNAPSHOT-shaded.jar   fs:$ROOT_DIR/dit/bin/

5.
rename exisiting tables in db

6. 
start processes:
java -jar $ROOT_DIR/dit/bin/ElsevierHarvester-1.0-SNAPSHOT-shaded.jar >> $ROOT_DIR/dit/bin/elsevier_harvester.log
java -jar $ROOT_DIR/dit/bin/ElsevierProcessor-1.0-SNAPSHOT-shaded.jar > $ROOT_DIR/dit/bin/elsevier_processor.log
